INV annual PM completed. with details:

Kyle and Eric completed the annual PM on 6/02/2025. Kyle and Eric shut the inverter down by keying off, AUX switch off, AC/DC switch off, LBD switch off in the field, and switch gear cabinet C OFF/Grounded. Kyle and Eric cleaned the inverter throughout all the doors, checked for any damage and leaks. After Kyle and Eric completed the inspection and found no issues Kyle and Eric removed all the LOTO and proceeded to turn the inverter back on.

notes: The technician inspected the String Power Controller 324, verified the light status, and traced the wiring to the charging module. They identified a loose connection with the Multi-Contact 4 connector and proceeded to reconnect it. This troubleshooting process ensured that the String Power Controller was functioning correctly after addressing the connection issue.
summary: Technician diagnosed and fixed connection issue.

notes: The technician reconnected the MC4 connector and utilized the return mode for the rack row to the east, allowing the String Power Controller battery to charge. After approximately ten minutes, the technician returned the String Power Controller to service, confirming that it was functioning properly. The issue was successfully resolved.
summary: Technician repaired tracking issue for Block 38C.
